### 4.1 Privacy by design — protection goals for AI use
_(per Standard Data Protection Model v3.1, Part D1.8)_

AI systems may only be used after the following data protection
protection goals have been deliberately addressed — as a design strategy, not
retroactively:

- **Data minimisation (Dm):** Do not bring more or different data into the AI context
  than necessary for the purpose. Anonymisation/pseudonymisation before prompt handover.
- **Unlinkability (Nn):** No linking of AI outputs with additional
  personal attributes without a legal basis. Purpose-specific pseudonyms.
- **Transparency (Tp):** Disclose AI use to data subjects (Art. 12-14
  GDPR + EU AI Act Art. 50). Audit trail of all AI decisions (Art. 12 AI Act).
- **Intervenability (Iv):** Data subjects can exercise their intervention rights (Art. 22(3)
  GDPR); single point of contact for AI-related access requests.
- **Confidentiality (Vt) + integrity (Ig):** TOMs pursuant to Art. 32 GDPR; validate
  output (Pydantic/Zod); do not pass LLM responses to the client unchecked.

